By Aisha Cole  Lagos –  The Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) says it is expecting 31 ships to bring petroleum products, food and other goods at the Apapa and Tin Can Island Ports, between Dec. 27 and Jan. 12, 2019. According to the NPA, four of the ships will sail in with petrol, the other 27 ships with buckwheat, general cargo, aviation fuel, steel, Aviation Turbine Kerosene (ATK), bulk gypsum and containers carrying different goods. It also said 25 ships had arrived at the ports and were waiting to berth with bulk wheat, general cargo, container, kerosene and petrol. (NAN)